
Cucumber Assignment


1. Difference between Cucumber and TestNG?



Cucumber - 1. Supports BDD Approach and it's helpful for Non-Technical StakeHolders.

		   2. Tests Steps were written in StepDefinitions under @Given, @when , @Then.
		   
		   3. By default it doesn't supports reports.
		   

TestNG -   1. TestNG is a TDD approach and have More Control on Test execution and it's helpful for automation testers.

           2. Tests were written and Executed under @Test Annotation.
           
           3. TestNG have inbuilt Reports , Assertions , Annotations , Priority.
           
           


2.Explain the use of When,Given,Then keywords


		1. Given When Then were the annotations used in the Cucumber Framework.
		
		2. Given - PreCondition of the Test
		
		   When - contains Action performed in the Test 
		   
		   Then - Assertion / Expected Result Validation.

























